This paper deals with sampling techniques for aggregate queries, which is a common problem in database systems (cs.DB). The paper also discusses lower bounds and algorithms for streaming data, which are topics in data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The concept of variance optimization is a key aspect of the paper, which falls under the category of machine learning and statistics (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the allocation of sample sizes, which is related to optimization and decision-making (cs.SI). Finally, the paper mentions information theory in the context of lower bounds for streaming algorithms (cs.IT).
